On January 31, 2005 Michael Jackson's molestation trial began with Jury selection. On February 15 Jackson was rushed to the hospital with the flu, delaying the jury selection in his trial for 3-4 days. Jackson left the hospital after being there 33 hours. On February 23 a jury was selected. After the jury was sworn in, attorneys began the selection of eight alternate jurors. On February 28 the trial judge revealed the detail of charges against Jackson and read the indictment that accused Jackson of molesting a 13 year old at his Neverland Ranch in 2003. 